HEADWORD: Lodicule
<hw>Lod"i*cule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lodicula</ets>. dim, of <ets>lodix</ets>, <ets>lodicis</ets>, a
coverlet: cf. F. <ets>lodicule</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One
of the two or three delicate membranous scales which are next to the
stamens in grasses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

